Borno Governor, Professor Babagana Umara Zulum on Tuesday at about 7:00pm arrived in Dikwa for humanitarian responses. The Governor was received by the Executive Chairman, Mohammed Alhaji Gumsama and some key stakeholders of the local government. Governor Zulum supervised and also got directly involved in the distribution of food and non-food items to a combined number of 40,000 Households in the community. Zulum traveled with the Member of House of Assembly representing Dikwa State Constituency, Hon. Zakariya Mohammed, Commissioners for Agriculture, Engr. Bukar Talba, Sugun Mai Male and Poverty Alleviation, Nuhu Clark, a number of humanitarian workers, officials and some APC chieftains. Governor Zulum in an interview said last year the community didnâ€™t have full access to their farmlands and most of their products were destroyed which necessitated the intention of the Government of Borno State to provide them with food and non-food items. The Governor announced the establishment of Mega Islamic School In Dikwa and assured them of getting agricultural input before the rainy season.